values:
What a beautiful afternoon!  I wish I could duck out of work early today.  Soooo much to do this weekend.  I haven't started any of my Christmas shopping yet.  Hopefully I have some time this weekend.  Saturday we're heading out to the hammer for the annual pot-luck dinner at Jesse & Taylor's. Yummm...I can't wait!  Hopefully the weather doesn't get too bad - I heard that we're supposed to get like 25cm of snow on Sunday.  I hate traveling in bad weather.

I went to see Dirty Dancing with Adam's mom last night.  OMG! what an awful show!  The show was so bad it was actually  funny.  People were laughing all throughout the show...at parts that aren't meant to be funny! "Nobody puts Baby in a corner!" HAHAHAHAHA...I almost peed my pants laughing at that one! Regardless of how bad the show was, we still had a great time.  I like spending time with my future mother-in-law...especially when it's just the two of us.  Drinks at the bar after the show were the best .  She is sooo funny!

I have to rent a car for over the holiday's and all the rental places around my apartment claim that they are sold out of vehicles for that time.  I've only tried booking online though.  So, I'm hoping that if I actually  go in, they can help me out.  How can they be sold out?  I would think they could transfer a car from another location to accommodate me???  Fingers crossed I can rent somewhere close to my place.  I really don't want to have to take the TTC arcoss the city just to pick up a car.  Why can't things just be easy????

Just when I think things are going well and everyone is happy, a certain someone I will refer to as "S", comes along and fucks everything up.  I'm so angry today.  I'm having trouble working.  People are annoying me with the smallest things.  I'm letting things bother me that I normally could care less about.  I really wish I could tell "S" how I feel but I'm forced to keep to myself and it's driving me NUTS!!!!!

Well, these last 2 weeks have certainly been painful...literally.  I had my wisdom teeth pulled 2 weeks ago and I'm still feeling the pain.  Long story short, I had a few complications with the extractions and then wound up with dry socket.  I'm still being treated for the dry socket, but I'm happy to report that I'm on my way to recovery.  Not being able to sleep or eat for that length of time really kicks your ass!  I can't wait until this is all over and I can go out for dinner and eat whatever I want!

I'm hoping this week goes by quickly.  Friday night is the Sons Of Butcher show at The Casbah, followed by a costume/keg party at Lindsay's bf's place.  Adam is opening ip for SOB and he's already got his costume - he's being Lemmy from Motorhead!  I still have no idea what I'm going to be.  I do this every year - I leave getting a costume until the last minute.  Any suggestions???

Did this week drag on for anyone else?  Jeez, it felt like Friday would never come!

Adam and I are heading back to the Hammer for the weekend.  Tonight is my mom's birthday and tomorrow we're introducing our grandparents to each other.  Should be a family-packed weekend! ;)  Hopefully we have time to see some friends while we're out there too.  I'm sure we'll get to the usual visit with Jesse & Taylor.  I'm keeping my fingers crossed we can see Jen & Joe too.  I still haven't seen her since hearing the news that she's pregnant!  I'm a bad friend.

Did anyone watch the premiere of The Office last night?  It was soo funny!  I watched the premiere of CSI too.  What a let down!  I hate it when they end shows that way...so predictable.

I've been thinking about getting a new tattoo alot lately.  I'll be 100% debt free in a few months and I'm really considering taking the money I put towards my line of credit to some fresh ink.  Adam will be so jealous!  I think its only fair that I get a new tat before he does.  OR, I could take that money and go on a trip somewhere.  Ahh...what to do???

My boss just got out of her meeting - I'd better get off LJ and get back to work before she sees me! 

Have a good weekend, everyone!

I can't believe September is almost over!  I get to look forward to having a week off after Thanksgiving, but then again, I'm dreading having my wisdom teeth pulled.  Yeah, that's exactly how I wanted to spend my vacation!  I guess it's better I do it now before I get any older.  Apparently, I'm old to be getting my wisdom teeth pulled.  The dentist told me that most people get them pulled in their late teens, early twenties.  I thought that was kinda weird, it's not like I'm old!?!  

Adam and I had a pretty fun weekend....pretty action packed for us these days! ;)  Ditch played the Indie club at the Edge on Saturday, so a bunch of us went downtown together to check them out.  The show was really good for that tiny little studio.  The vocals were a bit quiet but the band was tight and they played hard!  After the show a bunch of us came back to our place for UFC.  We were even treated to some mushroom karaoke, compliments of Shawn!  Adam and I were both pretty spent all day Sunday, so we abandoned all plans and stuck to the couch all day.  Wasting the day almost made it feel like a one day weekend though.  

Today was a painful Monday.  Started my day off with an argument with a  TTC collector.  Then, the subway was roasting hot and stopping for a couple minutes in between each stop.  Of course I'm standing beside the fat sweaty guy who's soaked his shirt in sweat.  Nice!  I felt like ass all morning and finally this afternoon, the crusty bitch, Marie, freaks out on me and a co-worker for talking too loudly ( we were having a normal conversation).    One day down, four to go...
Auuuggghh...I feel so sick right now.  Why did I eat that veggie dog and fries?  WHY?????
Holy Crap, I forgot all about my livejournal!  I think I'll start posting here again...starting tomorrow! ;)
